<html>
<head>
	<title>LAByrinth</title>	
	<meta charset="utf-8">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

	<link href="/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
	<link href="/css/bootstrap-theme.min.css" rel="stylesheet"> 
	<link href="/css/main.css" type="text/css" rel="stylesheet">
	
</head>
<body>

	<div class="navBar container-fluid">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-xs-4 current">
				<b><a href="stats"><img src="../images/person.png" height="10%" width="10%" alt="Profile" /></a></b>
			</div>
			<div class="col-xs-4 noncurrent">
				<b><a href="recipeSearch"><img src="../images/cookbook.png" height="8%" width="8%" alt="Recipes" /></a></b>
			</div>
			<div class="col-xs-4 noncurrent">
				<b><a href="options"><img src="../images/cog.png" height="10%" width="10%" alt="Options" /></a></b>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<br />
	<h1 align="center"> Profile </h1>
	
	<div align="center">
		<img src="images/profile.png" alt="ProfilePic">
		<h2> Lillian Lee </h2>
		<h3 style="margin-top: 30px"> Stats </h3>
		<p> Dishes cooked this month: <p id="output"></p></p>
		<p> Level : Beginner </p>
		<p> Favorite Food : Asian </p>
		<P> Disliked Food : Vegetable dishes </P>

	<div  style="margin-top: 40px" class="slideshow-container container-fluid">

		  <!-- Full-width images with number and caption text -->
		  <div class="mySlides">
		    <img src="images/Dishes.png" style="width:100%">
		    Febuary is almost over! Get some cooking in before its too late! 
		  </div>

		  <div class="mySlides">
		    <img src="images/Servings.png" style="width:100%">
		    Febuary is almost over! Get some cooking in before its too late! 
		  </div>

		  <div class="mySlides">
		    <img src="images/Types.png" style="width:100%">
		    You've made a lot of Asian dishes recently. We'll recommend you some more tasty asian dishes! 
		  </div>

		  <div class="mySlides">
		    <img src="images/Money.png" style="width:100%">
		    With the amount of money you've saved, you could buy a high powered gaming computer! 
		  </div>

	</div>
	<br>

	<!-- The dots/circles -->
	<div style="text-align:center">
	  <span class="dot" onclick="currentSlide(1)"></span> 
	  <span class="dot" onclick="currentSlide(2)"></span> 
	  <span class="dot" onclick="currentSlide(3)"></span> 
	  <span class="dot" onclick="currentSlide(4)"></span>
	</div>
		
	<p> <h4> Tip! </h4> You didn't cook too much this month. Maybe eat out less to save some money? </p>


	</div>
	
	<script src="js/scripts.js"></script>

	<script>
		window.onload=function(){
	document.getElementById('output').innerHTML= localStorage.getItem("count");
		}
	</script>
